
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `bunzip2` baraye baz kardane file-haye zip shode ba estefade az raveshe Bzip2 be kar miravad. Yani file-haye `.bz2` ra az halate zipeed dar miavarad va file asli ra dorost mikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `bunzip2 -k`  --> 💾 File asli zipeed shode ra hefz mikonad (keep).
    🔹 `bunzip2 -d`  --> 📤 Hamoon kare asli ro anjam mide, yani unzip mikone (decompress). (default)
    🔹 `bunzip2 -v`  --> 📢 Etela'at bishtar dar morede amal kardane dastoor namayesh mide (verbose).
    🔹 `bunzip2 -f`  --> 💪 Age file ghablan baz shode bood, majboor mikone ke dobare baz beshe (force).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ bunzip2 myfile.bz2

    🔹 File `myfile.bz2` ra baz mikonad va file `myfile` ra misazad.

    $ bunzip2 -k myfile.bz2

    🔹 File `myfile.bz2` ra baz mikonad va file `myfile` ra misazad, dar hale ke `myfile.bz2` ham hefz mishavad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ bunzip2 -v archive.bz2

    🔹 File `archive.bz2` baz mishavad, va etela'ati mesle andaze file ghabl va bad az baz shodan namayesh dade mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `bunzip2` command is used to decompress files that have been compressed using the Bzip2 algorithm. It essentially extracts `.bz2` files and restores them to their original state.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `bunzip2 -k`  --> 💾 Keeps the original compressed file.
    🔹 `bunzip2 -d`  --> 📤 Decompresses the specified file. (This is the default behavior).
    🔹 `bunzip2 -v`  --> 📢 Provides more detailed information about the decompression process (verbose).
    🔹 `bunzip2 -f`  --> 💪 Forces decompression, even if a file with the same name already exists (force).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ bunzip2 myfile.bz2

    🔹 Decompresses `myfile.bz2`, creating the file `myfile`.

    $ bunzip2 -k myfile.bz2

    🔹 Decompresses `myfile.bz2`, creating the file `myfile`, while also keeping the original `myfile.bz2`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ bunzip2 -v archive.bz2

    🔹 Decompresses the file `archive.bz2`, and shows verbose output, like the original and uncompressed file size.
